      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Eugene Waith Slide Collection (785 slides) Slides or architecture and scenery were taken by Professor Eugene Waith (English literature, emeritus) during his travels, and donated to the Visual Resources Collection in 1992. Slides of monuments and scenary on travels to Mexico, Britain, France, the Netherlands, Italy and Greece. Photographer is Eugene M. Waith, emeritus Professor of English Literature at Yale University. No identification on the slides. Minimal identification supplied by accompanying lists.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_arr1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>785 unlabeled 35 mm color slides in cardboard mounts, arranged in 24 projection cartridges (8 per box).</p>  
      </arrangement>
